%% vLLM CPU - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant vLLM as vLLM API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Engine as AsyncLLM Engine V1<br/>ZeroMQ IPC
    participant Model as PyTorch Model Executor<br/>CPU
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Prom as Prometheus Server

    Note over Client,Model: Flow 1: Inference Request (Chat Completion)
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Gateway->>RBAC: Forward (HTTPS/8443)<br/>Service Account Token
    RBAC->>vLLM: Forward (HTTP/8000)<br/>plaintext (pod-local)
    vLLM->>Engine: Process request<br/>ZeroMQ IPC
    Engine->>Model: Execute inference<br/>In-process function call
    Model-->>Engine: Generated tokens
    Engine-->>vLLM: Streaming results
    vLLM-->>Gateway: SSE stream response
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS streamed response<br/>TLS 1.2+

    Note over Engine,S3: Flow 2: Model Loading (startup)
    Engine->>HF: GET model weights<br/>Auth: HF Token (optional)
    HF-->>Engine: Model artifacts<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Engine->>S3: GET model weights (alternative)<br/>Auth: S3 credentials
    S3-->>Engine: Model artifacts<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Engine->>Model: Load model into memory

    Note over Prom,vLLM: Flow 3: Prometheus Metrics Scrape
    Prom->>vLLM: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP/8000 plaintext
    vLLM-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics response
